ay\", \"from\": 6107, \"to\": 6113}, {\"ngram\": \"superb form\", \"from\": 6146, \"to\": 6157}, {\"ngram\": \"more self-confidence\", \"from\": 6162, \"to\": 6182}, {\"ngram\": \"histhree stage victories\", \"from\": 6196, \"to\": 6220}, {\"ngram\": \"a logical favourite\", \"from\": 6274, \"to\": 6293}]}, {\"sentence\": \"After winning his first Tour de France stage, to become the first Black African to win at the Tour, Girmay wrote on social media: \\\"Let me open the door.\\\"\", \"from\": 6317, \"to\": 6470, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6341, \"end\": 6355, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"score\": 0.9999999992924131, \"rank\": 7.075281810730647e-10, \"text\": \"Tour de France\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Tour_de_France\"}, {\"begin\": 6383, \"end\": 6396, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"score\": 0.999999999994543, \"rank\": 5.199869884456748e-12, \"text\": \"Black African\", \"types\": [], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Black_people\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the Tour\", \"from\": 6407, \"to\": 6415}, {\"ngram\": \"Girmay\", \"from\": 6417, \"to\": 6423}, {\"ngram\": \"social media\", \"from\": 6433, \"to\": 6445}, {\"ngram\": \"the door\", \"from\": 6460, \"to\": 6468}]}, {\"sentence\": \"A medal in Paris would be historic, and gold would change cycling forever and blow open the door for many other African riders.\", \"from\": 6472, \"to\": 6599, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 6483, \"end\": 6488, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 5.467021451949361e-27, \"text\": \"Paris\", \"types\": [\"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Paris\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"A medal\", \"from\": 6472, \"to\": 6479}, {\"ngram\": \"gold\", \"fro